article.headline: Tournament MVP Watson scores 11
article.linkText: Washington forces 28 turnovers in upsetting Minnesota
article.story:
SEATTLE (AP) -- Cameo Hicks scored 14 points to help Washington
upset No. 14 Minnesota 72-67 in overtime Monday night.

In the final game of the WBCA Classic, the Huskies' pressure
defense forced the Gophers into 28 turnovers that led to 20 points.

A late 7-3 run by Washington (2-0) forced the game into overtime
after the teams exchanged leads for 20 minutes.

Breanne Watson, the tournament MVP, scored 11 points as
Washington defeated a non-conference, ranked opponent for the first
time since March 24, 2001, when the Huskies beat then-No. 7
Oklahoma.

Janel McCarville, who broke her left hand Oct. 28, missed her
second consecutive game for Minnesota (1-1).

Jamie Broback scored 18 points for Minnesota, but missed a
potential game-tying 3-pointer with less than two seconds
remaining.

Minnesota's last non-conference regular season loss was at
Stanford on Nov. 23, 2001.

Washington's Kayla Burt, who returned to action Sunday for the
first time since suffering cardiac arrest on New Year's Eve 2002,
scored five points. Teammate Kristen O'Neill added 10.
